               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation">1623</t:date>
                  <t:ab type="history">Gannata ʾIyasus is a Catholic church located in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1669Azazo">ʾAzazo</t:placeName> on the <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6546Wagan">ʾAṣe Wagan</t:placeName> hill. It was commissioned by <t:roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</t:roleName>
                     <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</t:persName> in <t:date>1621</t:date>, built
                     by the Jesuit <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7699Paez">Pedro Páez</t:persName> and consacrated
                     in <t:date>1623</t:date>. <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</t:persName> is
                     said to have laid the church's foundation stone and he was buried here. </t:ab>
               </t:note>
